Michelangelo's Prisoners at the Galleria dell'Accademia|https://www.florence-tickets.com/blog/florence/michelangelos-prisoners-at-the-galleria-dellaccademia|Accademia Gallery, in Florence, alongside the corridor leading to the famous David by  ...    The Prisons were left in Michelangelo's workshop in Florence, where they were found after his death by his nephew Leonardo Buonarroti. He decided to donate them to the Grand Duke Cosimo I de' Medici. In 1586 Bernardo Buontalenti placed the Prisons at the four corners of the Great Cave of the Boboli Gardens, which well suited the four statues in rough marble. And there they remained until 1908, perfectly stored away in the Cave, until their transfer to the Accademia Gallery in 1909. Italiano (IT)  English (US)  Español (ES)  [Français (FR)]
